{"body": "I don't see the point of adding this method.\r\n\r\nIf you pass only one id I prefer to use the `find.destroy!`. Multiples ids don't make sense since it will stop the execution in the first error and you will not know which elements were destroyed.\r\n\r\nCould you please you give us an example where you want to try to destroy multiple elements and is interesting to stop the execution in the middle?\r\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/21488003", "created_at": "2013-07-24T14:21:38Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10682#issuecomment-21488003", "updated_at": "2013-07-24T14:21:38Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 10682, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/rafaelfranca", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/0525b332aafb83307b32d9747a93de03?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F2c7b84fa30f0cea96a90729afe2970a0.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/received_events", "gravatar_id": "0525b332aafb83307b32d9747a93de03", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "rafaelfranca", "type": "User", "id": 47848, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237dc7dbd3543c1510089e3"}, "id": 21488003, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10682"}
